                    <span>Black females(African American, African, Caribbean, Afro-Latina) <br>have long been relegated to the margins by black men and whites(male and female)for so long.  The gathering of black women in New England in 1994 was a good start, but they need to be proactive in defending black women consistantly, whether concerning the negative portrayals by the media and society.  I think this book is a great start.</span>
                  
